<div style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold">		
	          <h1 align="center">Support the Project</h1>
<div align="center">
<p align="justify">The Margaret Sanger Papers Project and its digital edition is supported by grants from  <a href="https://www.nyu.edu/projects/sanger/project/funders.php">public and private foundations</a>  as well as individual donations. While it receives a good deal of in kind support from New York University, chiefly space and various services (photocopy, fax, digital access, library resources, postage, etc.), all of our salaries and research costs is funded though outside support.</p>
<p align="justify">While the Project has received the support of many foundations and federal agencies, our ability to complete our  work and our survival depends on the generosity of our supporters as well as readers of the <a href="https://www.nyu. edu/projects/sanger/newsletter/index.php">Project's Newsletter</a>. We will send complimentary copies of the Newslette r to all who donate at least $25. Donations to the Margaret Sanger Papers to help support these activities are tax deductible.</p>
<p align="justify">You may donate the through <a href="https://www.nyu.edu/giving/give-now/?id=1000061">NYU's giving site</a> or send checks, made payable to: <strong>New York University/Sanger Papers</strong> and sent to:</p>  
<div align="justify">
  <blockquote>
    <p>NYU Division of Libraries<br> 
      838 Broadway, Suite 504<br> 
      44 New York, NY 10003<br>
    </p>
	</blockquote>
    <p> We thank you very much for your support.</p>
  
    <h1 align="center">How You Can Help</h1>
<p align="justify">Support for documentary editions can take many forms. If you find the work of the Margaret Sanger Papers Project  useful, please take the time to let us know. In addition lobby your local research library to purchase the project's publications, in order to make these documents more widely accessible.</p>
	<h3 align="center">Lobby your Library</h3>
	<p align="justify">A list of the libraries that already own the Margaret Sanger Papers Microfilm Edition is available on this web site (<a href="http://www.nyu.edu/projects/sanger/publications/smith_series.php">Smith College Collections</a> /<a href="http://www.nyu.edu /projects/sanger/publications/collected_documents.php">Collected Documentss</a>)</p>
</p>
<div align="justify">Orders for <em>The Selected Papers of Margaret Sanger</em> can be made through the <a href="http://www.press.uillinois.edu/books/ordering.html">University of Illinois' web site</a> or through on-line booksellers such as <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Selected-Papers-Margaret-Sanger-1900-1928/dp/025202737X/ref=la_B001HOR0MO_1_3?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1436221638&sr=1-3">Amazon.com</a>. If you purchase the books through the link below, the Project will receive a small percentage of the purchase price as a donation.
    </p>   
</div>
<h3 align="center">Support Documentary Editing</h3>
  <p align="justify">Documentary editions, such as the Sanger Papers, are in trouble. Funding for these multi-year projects has become harder to come by, as federal agencies such as the <a href="http://www.archives.gov/nhprc/">National Historical Publications and Records Commission</a> (NHPRC) and <a href="ww.neh.gov">National Endowment for the Humanities</a> have faced budget cuts. Please support funding for these two agencies. For more information, or to get through the <a href="http://www.nhalliance.org/">National Humanities Alliance</a>. And finally, support the <a href="http://www.documentary
editing.org/wordpress/">Association for Documentary Editing</a></p>
   </div>			  
